Stands for Scan Formatted string

It uses format specifiers like printf e.g %d, %c, %s, e.t.c.

& is also called as address - of operator. Scanf needs to know the address of the variable in order to store the input of the user.

int main()
{
	int a, b;
	printf("Enter first number\n");
	scanf("%d", &a);
	printf("Enter second number\n");
	scanf("%d", &b);
	printf("%scanf("%d", &a);d + %d = %d", a, b, a+b);
	return 0;
}
